title: For Sale/Trade:  RARE INTERDYNAMIC KG-9 (LEGAL PRE KG-9 BAN)
postcontent:
Classified a machine gun by ATF. NO CLASS 3 Needed! (legal to own pre-ban)

The Interdynamic KG9 pistol was made in Miami Florida for a short time in the 1981-82 timeframe by Interdynamic of America, Inc. ATF decided in January 1982 that the gun was too easy to convert into a machine gun, and therefore decided that an unmodified open bolt semi-auto KG-9 was a machine gun. ATF exempted unmodified semi-auto KG-9 pistols made before this ruling from the scope of the ruling, so there are so-called grandfathered KG-9 pistols available in the USA. The KG-9 was based on a Swedish designed machine pistol, the MP-9. After the ATF ruling the gun was redesigned into a closed bolt, striker fired pistol, the Interdynamic KG-99, which was sold in the 1982-83 timeframe. After that Interdynamic went out of buisness. The original gun the cheap tec-9 was made to copy. Rare! Less than 1000 made! Look it up. I will trade for handguns too. There is a hairline crack in the bottom. It still works/shoots fine. 

Here is a video go the gun for sale http://youtu.be/3iUc8hX2938

title: For Sale/Trade:  7.62x51 (308) Spanish Mauser FR8, bolt action
location: not too far east of Indy, Indianapolis, Indiana
postcontent:
Offered for sale is a nice Spanish FR8 (Bolt action), shoots NATO 7.62 (308). These rifles were born of a need to arm second line troops, civil guard, and policemen when Spain adopted the G3/Cetme but did not have enough of them to go around. To solve this problem, Spain had all available Mausers on hand converted to 7.62x51, using CETME parts. The barrel, at 17.7 inches, is fitted with a flash hider that is compatible with then-NATO standard grenade launchers. The front sight is your standard CETME triple frame, with the barrel running through the middle hole. The bottom hole retains the cleaning kit, which resembles a gas block. The rear sight has one V notch and three apertures, the notch being for 100 meters, and the peeps progressively 200, 300, and 400 meters. The rifle holds 5 rounds of .308/7.62x51 in an internal magazine.

This rifle has been in storage since the mid 1980's. The parkerized finish is good, the wood is good and the barrel is clean. I have test fired it and it works as it should. I will include 200 rounds of 7.62x51 with purchase. 

Please FTF only in Indy metro area.

title: For Sale:  Interdynamic KG9
postcontent:
Classified a machine gun by ATF. NO CLASS 3 Needed! (legal to own pre-ban)

The Interdynamic KG9 pistol was made in Miami Florida for a short time in the 1981-82 timeframe by Interdynamic of America, Inc. ATF decided in January 1982 that the gun was too easy to convert into a machine gun, and therefore decided that an unmodified open bolt semi-auto KG-9 was a machine gun. ATF exempted unmodified semi-auto KG-9 pistols made before this ruling from the scope of the ruling, so there are so-called grandfathered KG-9 pistols available in the USA. The KG-9 was based on a Swedish designed machine pistol, the MP-9. After the ATF ruling the gun was redesigned into a closed bolt, striker fired pistol, the Interdynamic KG-99, which was sold in the 1982-83 timeframe. After that Interdynamic went out of buisness.

The original gun the cheap tec-9 was made to copy. Rare! Less than 1000 made! Look it up. 

Interdynamic KG-9 & 30 rd mag
